<h1>Adding Multiple Code Files to a GitHub Repository</h1>

<ol>
  <li>Create a New Folder:
    <ul>
      <li>In your GitHub repository, click the "Add file" button and select "Create new file".</li>
      <li>In the file name input, type the name of the new folder you want to create, followed by a forward slash (e.g., "my-code-files/").</li>
      <li>Click the "Commit new file" button to create the new folder.</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li>Add Files to the Folder:
    <ul>
      <li>Click on the new folder you just created to open it.</li>
      <li>Click the "Add file" button and select "Create new file".</li>
      <li>Name the new file with the appropriate file extension (e.g., "file1.py", "file2.js").</li>
      <li>Add your code to the file and click the "Commit new file" button to save the changes.</li>
      <li>Repeat the previous two steps to add more files to the folder.</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
</ol>
